    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>The olfaction core is a super-compact system of odor-detecting microprocessors and subcutaneous sensors that lets you determine the recent presence of a specific substance or even a person in a limited vicinity.</p>\n<p>By spending a minute in a 10-foot-square area, you can detect whether something has been within that area in the previous 24 hours; what you can detect is determined by the augmentation’s model. Mk 1 units can detect and identify most drugs and poisons. Mk 2 units can additionally detect and identify common types of explosives. Mk 3 olfaction cores function as mk 1 and mk 2 units and can additionally detect a specific individual you’ve had contact with or can otherwise identify the odor of.</p>\n<p>If you have blindsense (scent) or blindsight (scent), you need to spend only one round as a full action to use your olfaction core, and you can search a 25-foot-square area.</p>"
